<p xml:lang="tur"></p>
<p xml:lang="tur"></p>
<p xml:lang="tur"></p>
<p>The principal responsibility of the Ministry of Petroleum and Energy is to achieve a coordinated and integrated energy policy.</p>
<p>The Ministry has four departments, one department of administration and one staff department under the Secretary General.</p>
<p>The Ministry is under the lead of the Minister of Petroleum and Energy. The Minister has a staff with one state secretaries and one political advisor.</p>
<p>The Secretary General is the administrative leader of the Ministry. The Secretary General's staff is the Communication Unit and the secretarial staff.</p>
<p>The Minstry was established 1 June 1997 and has approx. 140 employees.</p>
